the biggest advantage a mage has in pvp is that their power is divided into two entities, and his opponent must ultimately choose who to deal with first. this desicion no matter what it is leaves them wide open to attacks from the other. <br>
for balance, thats also his biggest weakness. once the easier to control of the two (the pet) is delt with, then the mage is an easy target, since half his power is gone.<br>
<br>
if this were to apply to pvp, other players would find fighting mages almost like fighting 2 players. thats not balanced, thats overpowered.<br>
<br>
even though this change in its current form would be overpowered in pvp, thats not to say mages dont need help regarding pet resistances in pvp. its obvious mages need help, pets are way too easy to dispatch (root, fear, mez, snares, charm poofing). <br>
pets should get a pvp resistance and level boost, similarly to how casters suffer a 66% damage penalty. a boost not quite equal so that snaring a pet is like snaring the mage, but a boost none the less. <br>
<br>
i think the following would be more fair.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   pet resists and level should be what the pet has as a base, plus 75% the difference between pet and master</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
for example, say there is a mage with 200 resist in everything and level 60. the mages pet has 30 resist everything and is level 45. <br>
in pve, mobs would cast on the pet as if he had 200 resist everything and level 60 (100% of the master).<br>
in pvp, players would cast on the pet as if  he had 158 resist everything and was level 56.<br>
<br>
